G-MOE-GPU1-HYBRID — GPU residency campaign, rung 1: dense weights resident + dp4a GEMV (2026-07-02)
===================================================================================================
DESIGN (pure reuse — the 43.9x diffusion machinery): CPU-orchestrated qwen36_step keeps the
GDN recurrence, conv, MoE routing and expert dots on host; every BIG dense matmul (30x GDN
qkv/gate/out + 10x attn q/k/v/output + LM head) hits a RESIDENT packed weight on the 2060
via the existing upload_packed + gemv_w_packed (k_quant_act_int8 -> k_gemv_q4b/q8_dp4a_v2).

BUILT:
- cuda_forward.cu (ENGINE src): sp_q36gpu_{new,upload,matmul,free} — name-keyed DevTensor
  registry over upload_packed; per call H2D x (8-16KB), dp4a GEMV, D2H y, sync.
- forward_dispatch (MATH-CORE): sp_matmul_register_ext — an external hook with FIRST LOOK
  at every sp_matmul by weight name; 0=handled, nonzero=falls through to CPU. Unregistered
  = byte-identical null floor.
- harness: /DQ36_GPU + QWEN36_GPU=1 — uploads the dense set once (852.5 MB packed on
  device), registers the hook, runs the SAME qwen36_step.
KEY ENABLER (recon receipt): DevTensor.codes is EXACTLY the math-core arena layout — the
sp_frob_packed_tensor fields map 1:1; upload_packed takes the struct directly.

GATE (35B OK-container, real-vocab prompt, greedy 16, step+GPU):
  SEQ IDENTICAL 21/21 — through GPU int8 act-quant + dp4a, every near-tie held AGAIN.
  (760 6511 314 9338 369 11751 13 198 32 13 2912 198 33 13 3439 271 248068 271 8160 579 264)
  VERDICT: **GREEN** (pre-registered top-1 bar exceeded; the sequence has now survived
  scalar-serial, OMP, AVX2, batched, and GPU-dp4a arithmetic unchanged).

THE LADDER (16-token greedy, 35B-A3B, i9-11900KB + RTX 2060):
  stateless O(n^2)      0.018 tok/s
  + state decode        0.165        9.1x
  + OMP rows            1.136        6.8x
  + AVX2/dequant-free   1.605        1.41x
  + batch/parallel-if   1.655        1.03x
  + GPU dense resident  **3.312**    2.0x     (~0.31s/token flat; prefill 5 toks 1.59s)
  CUMULATIVE                        **184x**
Residual host time (~0.3s/tok) = CPU MoE experts + GDN recurrence/conv + per-call sync.

BUILD/LINK GOTCHAS (receipted):
- build-host-cuda-backend.bat outputs to ENGINE-ROOT build-host-cuda-backend/ (not
  tools/sp_daemon/...).
- The backend static lib BUNDLES its own math-core object copies (serial, no /openmp) ->
  linking it with the fast perf libs duplicates symbols. Experimental-harness fix: fast
  core libs FIRST + lld-link /FORCE:MULTIPLE (first definition wins = fast copies) +
  advapi32.lib. The production daemon link is unaffected. PROPER fix (follow-up): split the
  glue into its own object or make the backend build exclude core copies.
- clang-cl is NOT on env-cuda.bat's PATH (compile under env-cpu, run under env-cuda or add
  LLVM to PATH).

NEXT (GPU-2, the residency ladder proper): the 15GB expert set does not fit 12GB -> upload
HOT experts with an LRU (the dg_wcache machinery in cuda_forward.cu is exactly this pattern)
+ route expert_mm through a second hook; measure hit-rate on real prompts. Also: batch the
per-call H2D/D2H (ship the whole layer's activations once), and the head GEMV can subsume
the CPU argmax (k_argmax exists). Est: MoE off the host -> ~0.1s/token (~10 tok/s) before
any deeper work.
ENV: engine tree + submodule (this commit); RTX 2060 (852.5MB resident, ~10.5GB free);
clang-cl /openmp /arch:AVX2 /DQ36_GPU. Raw: _gen_gpu1.out.
